nodes.codification: New York General Business Law Article 39-F §§ 899-aa and 899-bb
nodes.name: New York Stop Hacks and Improve Electronic Data Security (SHIELD) Act
nodes.description: The SHIELD Act is New York's data security and breach notification law that amends the state's Information Security Breach and Notification Act, expands the scope of 'private information', and requires any person or business that owns or licenses private information of New York residents to implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards, enforced by the New York Attorney General.
nodes.base_regulation: New York Information Security Breach and Notification Act

nodes.heading: General Security Requirement
nodes.text: Any person or business that owns or licenses computerized data which includes private information of a resident of New York shall develop

nodes.heading: Compliant Regulated Entity Deemed Compliant
nodes.text: A person or business shall be deemed to be in compliance with paragraph (a) of this subdivision if it is a compliant regulated entity as defined in subdivision one of this section.

nodes.heading: Administrative Safeguards
nodes.text: Reasonable administrative safeguards such as the following...

nodes.heading: Designate Employee
nodes.text: Designates one or more employees to coordinate the security program.

nodes.heading: Identify Risks
nodes.text: Identifies reasonably foreseeable internal and external risks.

nodes.heading: Assess Safeguards
nodes.text: Assesses the sufficiency of safeguards in place to control the identified risks.

nodes.heading: Train Employees
nodes.text: Trains and manages employees in the security program practices and procedures.

nodes.heading: Service Providers
nodes.text: Selects service providers capable of maintaining appropriate safeguards

nodes.heading: Adjust Program
nodes.text: Adjusts the security program in light of business changes or new circumstances.

nodes.heading: Technical Safeguards
nodes.text: Reasonable technical safeguards such as the following...

nodes.heading: Assess Network/Software Design
nodes.text: Assesses risks in network and software design.

nodes.heading: Assess Processing/Storage Risks
nodes.text: Assesses risks in information processing

nodes.heading: Detect/Prevent Attacks
nodes.text: Detects

nodes.heading: Test and Monitor
nodes.text: Regularly tests and monitors the effectiveness of key controls

nodes.heading: Physical Safeguards
nodes.text: Reasonable physical safeguards such as the following...

nodes.heading: Assess Storage/Disposal Risks
nodes.text: Assesses risks of information storage and disposal.

nodes.heading: Detect/Prevent Intrusions
nodes.text: Detects

nodes.heading: Protect Unauthorized Access
nodes.text: Protects against unauthorized access to or use of private information during or after the collection

nodes.heading: Data Disposal
nodes.text: Disposes of private information within a reasonable amount of time after it is no longer needed for business purposes by erasing electronic media so that the information cannot be read or reconstructed.

nodes.name: Security Violation Penalty
nodes.description: Civil penalty for failing to maintain reasonable safeguards (per violation).

nodes.name: Notification Violation Penalty
nodes.description: Civil penalty for failing to notify residents (capped at $250k).

nodes.name: Statute of Limitations
nodes.description: Action must be brought within 3 years of notice or 6 years of breach.
